[B] Original work by Mx-Shell  —  All Rights Reserved by Mx-Shell
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Scope:
  - All complete prompt artifacts in 原始提示词/ marked
    "Source: mx-shell prompts collection" (Zombie Cleaner, Kamen Rider
    series, Kai'Sa, Pacific Rim+Gundam, Cyber-Wuxia, Metal Gear, etc.)
  - All quoted excerpts from Mx-Shell's livestream and document content,
    formatted as blockquotes or quoted strings across faq.md,
    credits.md, methodology.md, etc.

Sources and consent:

  All [B] content originates from two channels Mx-Shell himself
  voluntarily and publicly distributed:

    1. Prompt-and-troubleshooting documents he shared in his
       publicly-accessible fan group
       (mx-shell prompts + Q&A *.docx)
    2. His public Douyin livestream on May 12, 2026
       (livestream recording + text transcript)

  Mx-Shell explicitly expressed an open stance toward sharing.
  Direct quotes from the livestream:

    > "If you joined the fan group just to grab the prompts and then
    >  leave, fine, I don't mind."
    > "You can learn this, you can take it and do whatever — I don't
    >  care."
    > "I hope this lets the Chinese AI scene draw some inspiration
    >  from what I shared today, and that it can help people."

  This repository organizes the above public material as methodology
  extraction + reverence-style archival, with full source attribution.

  When using this section's content, please:

    1. Preserve attribution to Mx-Shell and source links
    2. Use only for study, research, and methodology reference
    3. Any commercial use (paid courses, training datasets, commercial
       AI model training, etc.) requires contacting Mx-Shell directly
    4. Do not redistribute the original text out of context
    5. The repo maintainer will respond immediately to any modification
       or removal request from Mx-Shell

  If Mx-Shell provides a formal written license, this section will be
  updated to reflect his chosen terms.

  Copyright (c) 2026 Mx-Shell.
  All rights reserved unless explicitly licensed otherwise.

